{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id912fe4ef-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s9527"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"9527"},"text":"§ 9527.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Sanctions with respect to investment in or facilitation of privatization of State-owned assets by the Russian Federation","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id912fe4f0-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s9527/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" In general","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"The President shall impose five or more of the sanctions described in ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t22/s9529"},"text":"section 9529 of this title","children":[],"tail":" if the President determines that a person, with actual knowledge, on or after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2017-08-02"},"text":"August 2, 2017","children":[],"tail":", makes an investment of $10,000,000 or more (or any combination of investments of not less than $1,000,000 each, which in the aggregate equals or exceeds $10,000,000 in any 12-month period), or facilitates such an investment, if the investment directly and significantly contributes to the ability of the Russian Federation to privatize state-owned assets in a manner that unjustly benefits—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id912fe4f1-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s9527/a/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" officials of the Government of the Russian Federation; or","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id912fe4f2-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s9527/a/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" close associates or family members of those officials.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id912fe4f3-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s9527/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Application of new sanctions","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"The President may waive the initial application of sanctions under subsection (a) with respect to a person only if the President submits to the appropriate congressional committees—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id912fe4f4-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s9527/b/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" a written determination that the waiver—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id912fe4f5-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s9527/b/1/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" is in the vital national security interests of the United States; or","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id912fe4f6-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s9527/b/1/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" will further the enforcement of this chapter; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id912fe4f7-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s9527/b/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" a certification that the Government of the Russian Federation is taking steps to implement the Minsk Agreement to address the ongoing conflict in eastern Ukraine, signed in Minsk, Belarus, on ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2015-02-11"},"text":"February 11, 2015","children":[],"tail":", by the leaders of Ukraine, Russia, France, and Germany, the Minsk Protocol, which was agreed to on "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2014-09-05"},"text":"September 5, 2014","children":[],"tail":", and any successor agreements that are agreed to by the Government of Ukraine."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id912fe4f8-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/44/tII/s233"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–44, title II, § 233","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2017-08-02"},"text":"Aug. 2, 2017","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/131/917"},"text":"131 Stat. 917","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id912fe4f9-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id912fe4fa-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"id912fe4fb-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"This chapter, referred to in subsec. (b)(1)(B), was in the original “this title”, meaning title II of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/44"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–44","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2017-08-02"},"text":"Aug. 2, 2017","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/131/898"},"text":"131 Stat. 898","children":[],"tail":", which is classified principally to this chapter. For complete classification of title II to the Code, see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/44/s201"},"text":"section 201 of Pub. L. 115–44","children":[],"tail":", set out as a Short Title note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t22/s9501"},"text":"section 9501 of this title","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
